<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1125,1692]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,1161,1188]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Original description:</emphasis>
“prossima alla 
<taxonomicName authority=", Monterosato" authorityName="Monterosato" box="[622,901,1162,1188]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" rank="variety" variety="conica">
var. 
<emphasis box="[669,744,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">conica</emphasis>
, Monterosato
</taxonomicName>
, ma più piccola e striata. Giri sei di color rossiccio con macchie rosse e bianche, con cordoncini sporgenti ed ombelico aperto” [shell similar to— 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="umbilicaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Gibbula umbilicaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.— 
<taxonomicName authority="Monterosato" authorityName="Monterosato" box="[265,537,1234,1260]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" rank="variety" variety="conica">
var. 
<emphasis box="[313,388,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">conica</emphasis>
Monterosato
</taxonomicName>
, but smaller and more striated. Shell of six whorls, reddish in colour with red and white flecks, with a protruding spiral sculpture and an open umbilicus].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="351" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1125,1692]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,456,1305,1332]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Remarks/New status:</emphasis>
having been instituted as a geographic race, we rank it subspecific, and thus available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[159,296,1341,1367]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 10, glossary). Considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[913,1398,1341,1368]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Steromphala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="umbilicaris">
<emphasis box="[913,1193,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Steromphala umbilicaris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1211,1390,1341,1368]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" refId="ref17590" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae, 824 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fasulo, G." box="[151,312,1377,1403]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="29 - 32" refId="ref16988" refString="Fasulo, G. (2012) Taxa di molluschi marini &quot; napoletani &quot; per toponimia. Notiziario S. I. M., 30 (2), 29 - 32." type="journal article" year="2012">Fasulo (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. Taking into account the figure alleged to its description (
<figureCitation box="[963,1052,1377,1403]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1375,1400]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,666,1347]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Gibbula (Magulus) ardens var. acutispira. Original figure. B, C. Gibbula ardens. B. Shells from Mar Morto (Miseno, Bacoli). C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 145, not numbered. D. Gibbula umbilicaris var. acherusiae. Original figures. E. Trochocochlea castriotae. Original figures. F. Gibbula (Magulus) biasoletti. Shells from Lido di Venezia and original label handwritten by Bellini. MCCIC—drawer 189, not numbered." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449570/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), as well as its peculiar shape and sculpture, we consider it here a misidentification for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Salis Marschlins, 1793)" authorityName="Salis Marschlins" authorityYear="1793" baseAuthorityName="Salis Marschlins" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[735,1188,1413,1439]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis box="[735,908,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Gibbula ardens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="von Salis Marschlins, C. U." box="[922,1180,1413,1439]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" refId="ref19667" refString="von Salis Marschlins, C. U. (1793) Reisen in verschiedne Provinzen des Konigreischs Neapel. 1. Ziegler &amp; Sons, Zurich und Leipzig, 442 pp." type="book" year="1793">Salis Marschlins, 1793</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and thus a new junior synonym of the latter taxon. This seems confirmed by the fact that R. Bellini was presumably not aware of the real identity of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Salis Marschlins" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[276,387,1485,1512]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis box="[276,387,1485,1512]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">G. ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
during his entire life (see also above in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini, 1903" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1903" box="[846,1287,1485,1512]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="ardens" variety="acutispira">
<emphasis box="[846,956,1485,1512]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">G. ardens</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1014,1128,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">acutispira</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[1135,1287,1485,1511]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="20 - 27" refId="ref15673" refString="Bellini, R. (1903 a) I molluschi del Lago Fusaro e del Mar Morto nei Campi Flegrei. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 16, 20 - 27." type="journal article" year="1903">Bellini, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). In fact, this 
<taxonomicName box="[151,281,1521,1548]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" rank="variety" variety="was">variety was</taxonomicName>
then subsequently ascribed by the same author to 
<taxonomicName authority="Recluz" authorityName="Recluz" box="[852,1299,1521,1548]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="agathensis" subGenus="Colliculus">
<emphasis box="[852,944,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Gibbula</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[961,1076,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Colliculus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1094,1214,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">agathensis</emphasis>
Recluz
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref15827" refString="Bellini, R. (1929 a) I molluschi del Golfo di Napoli (studi precedenti, l'ambiente, enumerazione e sinonimia). Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli, 6 (2), 1 - 87." type="journal article" year="1929">Bellini 1929</bibRefCitation>
), now considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Payraudeau, 1826) (Molluscabase 2019 a)" authorityName="Molluscabase" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Payraudeau" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[651,1398,1557,1584]" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Steromphala" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adansonii">
<emphasis box="[651,911,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">Steromphala adansonii</emphasis>
(Payraudeau, 1826) (Molluscabase 2019a)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Salis Marschlins" baseAuthorityYear="1793" class="Gastropoda" family="Trochidae" genus="Gibbula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ardens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="351">G. ardens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not found during samplings held in the area in 
<date box="[813,939,1593,1620]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" value="1975" valueMax="2018">1975–2018</date>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Russo, G. F. &amp; Ferro, R." box="[954,1188,1593,1620]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref18911" refString="Russo, G. F. &amp; Ferro, R. (1980) Le biocenosi bentoniche del lago Fusaro. I-Osservazioni faunistiche. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, 89, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1980">Russo &amp; Ferro 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferro, R. &amp; Russo, G. F." box="[1200,1431,1593,1620]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="191 - 198" refId="ref17059" refString="Ferro, R. &amp; Russo, G. F. (1981) Aspetti di particolare interesse nella malacofauna del Lago Fusaro. Bollettino Malacologico, 17 (7 - 8), 191 - 198." type="journal article" year="1981">Ferro &amp; Russo 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferro, R. &amp; Russo, G. F." box="[151,210,1629,1655]" pageId="8" pageNumber="351" pagination="3 - 19" refId="ref17097" refString="Ferro, R. &amp; Russo, G. F. (1982) Le biocenosi bentoniche del Lago Fusaro. II-Malacofauna. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, 91, 3 - 19." type="journal article" year="1982">1982</bibRefCitation>
; authors’ unpublished data), and therefore it presumably did not survive the anthropogenic changes to which the Fusaro Lake has been subjected in the last century.
</paragraph>
